commit.message: Compile fixes (gcc6, Debian stretch)
Edited Redundant macros
Notice development moved to github
Documented stickWM
Updated licence, and install instructions.

Removed 'sed' uglyness from Makefile.
Included config.mk with version, dependencies and debug flags.
updated email address
Changed licence to GPL 3, and included copyright notice.
Updated website, and corrected SVN checkout instructions, email, etc.
Use sed instead of perl in the makefile (Raphael Droz)
Added a clean make target (Raphael Droz)
inotify.h is now provided with libc6. Use that instead of shipping our own (Raphael Droz)
Fix segfault on invalid config (Stephen Wattam)
Fixed dependencies in README (a long long time ago, but forgot to commit).
xnots is in portage. Deleting unofficial ebuild.

Version bump to 0.2.1.
    1. Added dependency on xrandr, so that screen size changes can be detected.
    2. Bugfix -- when screen size is increased, background of transparent notes was wrong.
    3. Added moveOnScreenResize option by which the relative position of notes on the screen is kept constant when the screen is resized.
Exclude SVN files from the distfile.

1. Made debugging info an option that can be passed to make
2. Add -fno-strict-aliasing to CFLAGS to suppress compile warnings
Committed local modifications
Put mans in /usr/share/man, and not /usr/man
Added TODO
Version bump to 0.2
Fixed 'make dist' option in Makefile
Added xext to CFLAGS, just in case
Fixed compile on FC5
minor changes to Makefile
added .xnotsinfo for example note directory

1. Version bump to 0.11
2. Accepts config file and notes directory as command line options like
   standard unix programs.
Download instruction changes (added tags/xnots-X.X svn instructions)

Removed xnots.1.txt from svn control, and added a rule in Makefile to generate
it from the man page.
